From be2163d94acb9952f6f7cfed4d41171e0912f5b6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adrien Cossa <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:06:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(agents): inject loaded-skill preamble into raw
 Agent-tool sub-agent briefs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A sub-agent spawned through the raw harness Agent tool gets only its thin subagent-type system prompt — it never receives the SKILL.md bodies the orchestrator has loaded. The headless dispatch path already embeds skills (build_system_context / _read_skill_contents), but an orchestrator that spawns sub-agents with a bare prompt string bypasses that injection, so the sub-agent over-provisions for remote e2e, runs raw playwright/glab instead of t3, and ignores overlay rules.

Mechanism: the skill-content rendering concern moves into teatree.agents.skill_injection (a Django-free module). build_subagent_skill_preamble() concatenates each requested skill's SKILL.md body into a dispatch preamble, resolving names across the framework skills dir AND the active overlay's skills dir (so t3-<overlay> skills embed too). The command t3 <overlay> skill-preamble --skills t3:rules,t3:e2e[,<overlay-skill>] emits that preamble for the orchestrator to prepend to every Agent-tool brief; it fails loud (non-zero) on an unresolved skill rather than ship a brief that silently dropped a rule set.

Contract: rules/SKILL.md section Sub-Agent Limitations now requires every raw Agent-tool spawn to carry the preamble; the dispatched prompt must contain the embedded SKILL.md bodies, not a bare task description. BLUEPRINT skill-bundle section updated to match.

Eval: orchestrator_embeds_skills_in_subagent_brief pins it — the _fail fixture (bare-brief spawn) is graded a failure, the _pass fixture (preamble-embedded spawn) is graded a pass, the _noop fixture is graded a failure, and removing the matchers flips the _fail verdict to a pass (teeth check).

Open questions and assumptions: (1) Spelled the command t3 <overlay> skill-preamble rather than nesting it under agent — agent is an existing leaf launch command and a Typer group with a positional task argument shadows subcommand routing (verified); a sibling leaf avoids breaking t3 <overlay> agent <task> (assumed). (2) Scenario lives in tests/eval_lanes/scenarios/ (the core catalog), hand-written like main_clone_protected.yaml — the restructured scenarios tree named in the brief is not present on origin/main (assumed). (3) Pre-existing and unrelated: backlog-sweep is an uncovered eval gap on clean origin/main (test_skill_eval_coverage), left untouched (open).
